  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\n`forge script` when using with large contracts / libraries that exceed EIP-170 size limit, asks following confirmation:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[⠰] Compiling...\r\nNo files changed, compilation skipped\r\nScript ran successfully.\r\n`Unknown8` is above the EIP-170 contract size limit (128607 > 24576).\r\n`Unknown9` is above the EIP-170 contract size limit (128972 > 24576).\r\n`Unknown21` is above the EIP-170 contract size limit (128972 > 24576).\r\n`Unknown22` is above the EIP-170 contract size limit (31574 > 24576).\r\n`NovaVerifierContract` is above the EIP-170 contract size limit (37490 > 24576).\r\nDo you wish to continue? [y/n] \r\n```\r\n\r\nwhich can be difficult to handle in tty-disabled environments like docker containers. It would be nice to have `-n`, `-y` flags that can be submitted to `forge script` which disable mentioned interactive prompt.\r\n\r\nP.S.: [Solutions](https://askubuntu.com/questions/338857/automatically-enter-input-in-command-line) like `yes | forge script` also don't work in no-tty env.\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
